---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="The Seven Moedim — Yahuah's Appointed Times | Nazaryah"
  description="The moedim of Yahuah are not Old Testament holidays or Jewish customs — they are the dates He uses to do His work. Pesach, Hag HaMatzot, Bikkurim, Shavuot, Yom Teruah, Yom Kippur, Sukkot, and the Eighth Day, walked through one at a time."
>
  <main class="cf-index">

    <div class="cf-index-inner">

      <a href="/calendar" class="cf-index-back"><span class="arrow">←</span><span>Back to the Calendar</span></a>

      <header class="cf-index-header">
        <p class="cf-index-eyebrow">— Category VIII &middot; The Seven Moedim —</p>
        <h1 class="cf-index-title">The Seven Moedim</h1>
        <p class="cf-index-subtitle">The appointed times Yahuah set into His own creation as the framework for His redemption work — past, present, and yet to come.</p>
      </header>

      <section class="cf-studies-grid">

        <a href="/calendar/seven-moedim/importance" class="cf-study">
          <p class="cf-study-num">Study 1</p>
          <h3>The Importance of the Moedim</h3>
          <p>The moedim are not Old Testament holidays or Jewish customs. Yahuah calls them <em>"my feasts"</em> in His own words. They are the dates He has historically used to act, the framework His redemption story is written on, and the pattern hidden in plain sight throughout Scripture.</p>
          <span class="cf-study-cta">Read the Study →</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/calendar/seven-moedim/pesach" class="cf-study">
          <p class="cf-study-num">Study 2</p>
          <h3>Pesach — The Meal Under the Blood</h3>
          <p>Pesach is the meal of the 14th of Aviv, eaten under the blood while the destroyer passes by outside. Yahushua died at the very hour the Pesach lambs were slaughtered. Why the Last Supper was a preparation meal — not the Pesach — and why the leavened bread on the table proves it.</p>
          <span class="cf-study-cta">Read the Study →</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/calendar/seven-moedim/hag-hamatzot" class="cf-study">
          <p class="cf-study-num">Study 3</p>
          <h3>Hag HaMatzot — The Seven-Day Cleansing</h3>
          <p>The seven days of unleavened bread that follow the Pesach meal. Pesach is the door; Hag HaMatzot is the room you walk into. Yahushua's sinless body in the tomb during the very feast that pictures a body without corruption, and the 7½-day pattern echoed in Revelation's silence in heaven.</p>
          <span class="cf-study-cta">Read the Study →</span>
        </a>

      </section>

    </div>

  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .cf-index {
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #0e0905 0%, #1a110a 25%, #160f07 100%);
    color: #b8a584;
    font-family: 'Crimson Pro', 'EB Garamond', Georgia, serif;
    min-height: 100vh;
    padding: 4.5rem 1.5rem 6rem;
  }

  .cf-index-inner { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; }

  .cf-index-back {
    display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem;
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif; font-size: 0.7rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em; text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #8a7855; text-decoration: none;
    margin-bottom: 3rem; padding: 0.5rem 0.9rem 0.5rem 0.65rem;
    border: 1px solid #2a1a08; background: rgba(10, 6, 2, 0.4);
    font-weight: 600;
    transition: color 0.2s, border-color 0.2s, padding 0.2s;
  }
  .cf-index-back:hover { color: #c9a961; border-color: #4a3218; padding-left: 0.5rem; }
  .cf-index-back .arrow { font-size: 1em; transition: transform 0.2s; }
  .cf-index-back:hover .arrow { transform: translateX(-3px); }

  .cf-index-header { text-align: center; margin-bottom: 4rem; max-width: 720px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; }
  .cf-index-eyebrow { font-family: 'Cinzel', serif; font-size: 0.78rem; letter-spacing: 0.32em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #8a7855; font-weight: 600; margin: 0 0 1.2rem; }
  .cf-index-title { font-family: 'Cinzel', serif; font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 5vw, 3.4rem); font-weight: 700; color: #f0e0bf; margin: 0 0 1rem; letter-spacing: 0.025em; line-height: 1.12; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .cf-index-subtitle { font-family: 'Crimson Pro', Georgia, serif; font-style: italic; font-size: 1.1rem; color: #b8a584; line-height: 1.65; margin: 0; }

  .cf-studies-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 1.5rem; }

  .cf-study {
    display: flex; flex-direction: column;
    text-decoration: none; color: inherit;
    background: #1a110a;
    border: 1px solid rgba(180, 140, 80, 0.18);
    border-top: 3px solid #c9a961;
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 2rem 1.6rem 1.6rem;
    transition: background 0.25s, border-color 0.25s, transform 0.2s;
  }
  .cf-study:hover { background: #221710; border-color: rgba(200, 160, 100, 0.34); border-top-color: #d4a04a; transform: translateY(-2px); }

  .cf-study-num { font-family: 'Cinzel', serif; font-size: 0.7rem; letter-spacing: 0.24em; color: #a88b4f; margin: 0 0 1rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .cf-study h3 { font-family: 'Cinzel', serif; font-size: 1.15rem; font-weight: 700; color: #f0e0bf; margin: 0 0 1rem; line-height: 1.25; letter-spacing: 0.015em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .cf-study > p { font-family: 'Crimson Pro', Georgia, serif; color: #b8a584; font-size: 0.96rem; line-height: 1.65; flex: 1; margin: 0 0 1.4rem; }
  .cf-study-cta { font-family: 'Cinzel', serif; font-size: 0.7rem; letter-spacing: 0.22em; color: #c9a961; text-transform: uppercase; font-weight: 600; transition: color 0.2s; }
  .cf-study:hover .cf-study-cta { color: #f0e0bf; }

  @media (max-width: 900px) { .cf-studies-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
  @media (max-width: 520px) { .cf-index { padding: 3rem 1.1rem 4rem; } }
</style>
